reviewText: Everything was voiced over, the audio went from loud to quiet constantly, the acting sucked, and everything was just trash. Not worth a single dollar, let alone 15.

Definitely kind of a crappy movie. There were a few redeeming qualities, and scenes. One of which being that me and my husband were unpaid extras in this movie. So that's cool. If you have no reason other than someone you know was in or helped on this movie, don't buy it. You will be disappointed. Overall, 2 out of 5 on a good day.
The cinematography is great for an independent film.
